-- Sharp R&D Section Plans to Make English Official Language, Sankei Reports
-- B y   K a z u y o   S a w a
-- 2010-10-27T23:06:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/sharp-resarch-section-plans-to-make-english-official-language-sankei-says.html
Sharp Corp. plans to make English
the official language of a research and development group next
fiscal year, the Sankei newspaper reported, without citing
anyone.   It will be the first time part of a major Japanese
electronics company has adopted English as an official language,
the newspaper said. The department, which developed the Aquos
LCD television, operates in Japan, the U.S. and U.K., the report
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kazuyo Sawa in Tokyo at 
 ksawa3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Fergus Maguire at 
 fmaguire@bloomberg.net  